WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:16.016 --> 00:00:18.351 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] All right,
who's ready to start the show?

00:00:18.435 --> 00:00:20.562 position:50% align:center
<i>Konnichiwa</i> !

00:00:20.645 --> 00:00:23.690 position:50% align:center
I'm Uramichi, and I'm
your gymnast Oniisan!

00:00:23.773 --> 00:00:25.567 position:50% align:center
It's time for
<i>Together with Maman</i> ,

00:00:25.650 --> 00:00:27.652 position:50% align:center
so let's have some fun!

00:00:27.736 --> 00:00:29.654 position:50% align:center
Everybody, gather round!

00:00:29.738 --> 00:00:32.991 position:50% align:center
Time to come hang out
with your big bro!

00:00:35.577 --> 00:00:38.538 position:50% align:center
Is he more pumped up than
usual or am I imagining it?

00:00:38.621 --> 00:00:39.831 position:50% align:center
[GIRL B]
It's hard to watch.

00:00:39.914 --> 00:00:43.084 position:50% align:center
[BOY A] Uramichi Oniisan
has his ups and downs.

00:00:43.168 --> 00:00:44.544 position:50% align:center
Great!

00:00:44.627 --> 00:00:46.838 position:50% align:center
Now it's time for everyone's
favorite part of the show.

00:00:46.921 --> 00:00:49.174 position:50% align:center
Let's all do the ABC Exercise!

00:00:49.257 --> 00:00:51.801 position:50% align:center
Ready? Follow me!

00:00:54.929 --> 00:00:59.100 position:50% align:center
[GIRL A] Ooh, I think he
just crashed pretty hard.

00:00:59.184 --> 00:01:01.227 position:50% align:center
Hey, kids! Wow!

00:01:01.311 --> 00:01:03.897 position:50% align:center
This seems like a great
learning moment to me!

00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:06.566 position:50% align:center
[GIRL B]
Huh. Guess he's okay now.

00:01:06.649 --> 00:01:10.111 position:50% align:center
See, once you get to be
as old as your Oniisan,

00:01:10.195 --> 00:01:12.447 position:50% align:center
your brain has already scheduled
your moods for the day

00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:14.074 position:50% align:center
by the time you wake up.

00:01:14.157 --> 00:01:15.617 position:50% align:center
I couldn't say why.

00:01:15.700 --> 00:01:16.826 position:50% align:center
Maybe it's to prevent itself

00:01:16.910 --> 00:01:19.204 position:50% align:center
from pushing your body
beyond its limits.

00:01:19.287 --> 00:01:21.748 position:50% align:center
But sometimes,
fail-safes can fail.

00:01:21.831 --> 00:01:22.916 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Uh?

00:01:22.999 --> 00:01:24.793 position:50% align:center
So right now, I'm on
pace to burn through

00:01:24.876 --> 00:01:27.379 position:50% align:center
70% of today's energy
supply before lunch.

00:01:27.462 --> 00:01:29.214 position:50% align:center
And as my brain
shakes itself apart,

00:01:29.297 --> 00:01:32.467 position:50% align:center
my mood starts to become
erratic, like you saw just now.

00:01:32.550 --> 00:01:35.970 position:50% align:center
[GIRL C]
Please don't die, Oniisan.

00:01:36.054 --> 00:01:37.764 position:50% align:center
But it's all
<i>daijoubu</i> , kids!

00:01:37.847 --> 00:01:40.892 position:50% align:center
I can run on fumes till the
end of the day if I have to!

00:01:40.975 --> 00:01:42.394 position:50% align:center
That's what grown-ups do!

00:01:42.477 --> 00:01:45.105 position:50% align:center
[BOY A] I don't wanna be
that kind of grown-up.

00:03:15.987 --> 00:03:18.907 position:50% align:center
Okay! Time to gather
round, kids!

00:03:18.990 --> 00:03:21.951 position:50% align:center
[KIDS cheering, laughing]

00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:24.954 position:50% align:center
Easy! No pushing
or shoving, please!

00:03:25.038 --> 00:03:26.873 position:50% align:center
Hm?

00:03:26.956 --> 00:03:28.416 position:50% align:center
What's this?

00:03:29.376 --> 00:03:31.628 position:50% align:center
Is something the matter,
Kazuki- <i>kun</i> ?

00:03:31.711 --> 00:03:33.004 position:50% align:center
You look a bit down.

00:03:33.088 --> 00:03:35.298 position:50% align:center
Maybe you'll feel better
if you come play with us.

00:03:35.382 --> 00:03:37.258 position:50% align:center
[KAZUKI]
Mh-mh.

00:03:37.342 --> 00:03:39.386 position:50% align:center
You don't feel like it, huh?

00:03:39.469 --> 00:03:41.221 position:50% align:center
Well, if you don't wanna
play with everybody,

00:03:41.304 --> 00:03:43.556 position:50% align:center
do you think you
can explain why?

00:03:43.640 --> 00:03:46.851 position:50% align:center
[KAZUKI]
Umm... Mh-mh.

00:03:46.935 --> 00:03:48.478 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Hm?

00:03:48.561 --> 00:03:50.230 position:50% align:center
We should just leave
him alone, Oniisan.

00:03:50.313 --> 00:03:52.565 position:50% align:center
He's been like that
the whole time today.

00:03:52.649 --> 00:03:54.192 position:50% align:center
He won't talk to anybody.

00:03:54.275 --> 00:03:56.945 position:50% align:center
Forget him! We all wanna play!

00:03:57.028 --> 00:04:01.950 position:50% align:center
Look, buddy, to be honest,
there's a lot of times

00:04:02.033 --> 00:04:05.245 position:50% align:center
when I just don't feel like
doing something, either.

00:04:05.328 --> 00:04:08.957 position:50% align:center
But no one ever says,
"Leave him alone."

00:04:09.040 --> 00:04:11.418 position:50% align:center
And it's not because
they're concerned for me.

00:04:11.501 --> 00:04:13.586 position:50% align:center
It's because if I'm
not doing my part,

00:04:13.670 --> 00:04:15.171 position:50% align:center
business grinds to a halt.

00:04:15.255 --> 00:04:17.257 position:50% align:center
That's why we have to
learn an important skill

00:04:17.340 --> 00:04:19.968 position:50% align:center
we call "going along
to get along."

00:04:20.051 --> 00:04:21.261 position:50% align:center
It's where you do
what you're told

00:04:21.344 --> 00:04:22.554 position:50% align:center
even if you don't want to,

00:04:22.637 --> 00:04:26.016 position:50% align:center
so you can say it's
done and clock out.

00:04:26.099 --> 00:04:27.434 position:50% align:center
Try and learn it in a nice,

00:04:27.517 --> 00:04:30.395 position:50% align:center
low-pressure environment
while you can.

00:04:32.272 --> 00:04:35.442 position:50% align:center
Kazuki- <i>kun</i> , one day,
you're going to miss the times

00:04:35.525 --> 00:04:37.152 position:50% align:center
when people saw you
in a bad mood

00:04:37.235 --> 00:04:39.029 position:50% align:center
and decided to give
you some space.

00:04:39.112 --> 00:04:40.697 position:50% align:center
That's truly a privilege.

00:04:40.780 --> 00:04:42.282 position:50% align:center
Uh. I'll play, too.

00:04:42.365 --> 00:04:44.200 position:50% align:center
You wanna play, too?

00:04:44.284 --> 00:04:47.787 position:50% align:center
Hey, guys! Good news.
Kazuki- <i>kun</i> wants to play!

00:04:47.871 --> 00:04:50.790 position:50% align:center
That's great! Let's all give
him a big welcome, okay?

00:04:50.874 --> 00:04:52.208 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Okay!

00:04:52.292 --> 00:04:55.253 position:50% align:center
Now, we're still waiting
on a few friends.

00:04:55.337 --> 00:04:58.715 position:50% align:center
Usao- <i>kun</i> and Kumao- <i>kun</i> .
Should we call them?

00:04:58.798 --> 00:04:59.758 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:04:59.841 --> 00:05:01.760 position:50% align:center
I'm seriously asking
if you want to,

00:05:01.843 --> 00:05:03.511 position:50% align:center
'cause we don't have to.

00:05:03.595 --> 00:05:07.766 position:50% align:center
Wait, we don't? Seriously?
But we should, right?

00:05:07.849 --> 00:05:08.808 position:50% align:center
You think?

00:05:08.892 --> 00:05:09.934 position:50% align:center
Well, aren't you a good kid,

00:05:10.018 --> 00:05:12.020 position:50% align:center
thinking about your
friends like that?

00:05:12.103 --> 00:05:14.647 position:50% align:center
Now, let's call out to
Usao- <i>kun</i> and Kumao- <i>kun</i>

00:05:14.731 --> 00:05:17.150 position:50% align:center
as loud as we can,
okay, everybody?

00:05:17.233 --> 00:05:18.943 position:50% align:center
Ready and...

00:05:19.027 --> 00:05:24.240 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Usao- <i>kun</i> ! Kumao- <i>kun</i> !

00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:26.993 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] C'mon, Kumatani,
I'm beggin' you, man!

00:05:27.077 --> 00:05:28.870 position:50% align:center
I swear, I'll pay you
back next month,

00:05:28.953 --> 00:05:30.747 position:50% align:center
no matter what I gotta do!

00:05:30.830 --> 00:05:31.915 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
Get off me.

00:05:31.998 --> 00:05:33.833 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Seriously,
I gotta pay my rent!

00:05:33.917 --> 00:05:36.127 position:50% align:center
Otherwise, my landlord
is legally obligated

00:05:36.211 --> 00:05:37.504 position:50% align:center
to throw me out on the street!

00:05:37.587 --> 00:05:38.922 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
You're heavy.

00:05:39.005 --> 00:05:41.383 position:50% align:center
And it's your own damn
fault you're broke!

00:05:41.466 --> 00:05:42.384 position:50% align:center
Who burned all your money

00:05:42.467 --> 00:05:44.260 position:50% align:center
on pachinko and
mahjong, exactly?

00:05:44.344 --> 00:05:45.804 position:50% align:center
You did.

00:05:45.887 --> 00:05:47.430 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Uh, yeah, but--

00:05:47.514 --> 00:05:49.641 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
There is no "but"!

00:05:49.724 --> 00:05:52.894 position:50% align:center
And either way, you already
owe me 20,000 yen!

00:05:52.977 --> 00:05:54.104 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Wait, you remembered about that?

00:05:54.187 --> 00:05:55.772 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
Buy a tent.

00:05:57.023 --> 00:05:58.733 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Please, Kumatani.

00:05:58.817 --> 00:06:02.278 position:50% align:center
We're friends,
aren't we? BFFs, right?

00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:03.405 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
That's the last approach

00:06:03.488 --> 00:06:05.532 position:50% align:center
you should be trying
to take right now.

00:06:05.615 --> 00:06:06.991 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
I'm sorry, okay?

00:06:07.075 --> 00:06:09.369 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
Go ask Uramichi for the cash.

00:06:09.452 --> 00:06:11.538 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Ugh. "Die," you mean.

00:06:11.621 --> 00:06:13.707 position:50% align:center
Man, this has me
missin' our dorm days,

00:06:13.790 --> 00:06:16.042 position:50% align:center
back before I had
to think about rent.

00:06:16.126 --> 00:06:17.669 position:50% align:center
It was so easier to
get everyone together

00:06:17.752 --> 00:06:19.879 position:50% align:center
for drinks back then, too.

00:06:19.963 --> 00:06:22.549 position:50% align:center
Uramichi's apartment
is just far enough away.

00:06:22.632 --> 00:06:25.427 position:50% align:center
Making the whole trip is
kind of a pain in the ass.

00:06:25.510 --> 00:06:27.012 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
It's a real pain in my ass

00:06:27.095 --> 00:06:28.805 position:50% align:center
when you make the trip, too.

00:06:28.888 --> 00:06:30.724 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Huh? Ah!

00:06:30.807 --> 00:06:32.892 position:50% align:center
But missing your cue in
two different languages

00:06:32.976 --> 00:06:34.728 position:50% align:center
is the biggest pain of all.

00:06:34.811 --> 00:06:38.189 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Ah! I'm so sorry!
I'm so sorry! We're coming!

00:06:38.273 --> 00:06:41.026 position:50% align:center
Also, while we're here,
I could use some help with rent.

00:06:41.109 --> 00:06:44.195 position:50% align:center
You think this is
the time? Seriously?

00:06:44.279 --> 00:06:45.613 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA chuckles]

00:06:46.531 --> 00:06:48.074 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Okay, kids!

00:06:48.158 --> 00:06:49.743 position:50% align:center
I finally found
our furry friends,

00:06:49.826 --> 00:06:51.619 position:50% align:center
Usao- <i>kun</i> and Kumao- <i>kun</i> !

00:06:51.703 --> 00:06:53.455 position:50% align:center
Let's enjoy the time
we have with them

00:06:53.538 --> 00:06:55.874 position:50% align:center
because they might not
be back tomorrow!

00:06:55.957 --> 00:06:58.209 position:50% align:center
And if they're not, remember,
they're just hibernating,

00:06:58.293 --> 00:07:00.420 position:50% align:center
so there's no need
to worry about them!

00:07:00.503 --> 00:07:03.506 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Please. I can't
afford to lose this job.

00:07:03.590 --> 00:07:06.843 position:50% align:center
Where do you two live anyway,
Usao- <i>kun</i> and Kumao- <i>kun</i> ?

00:07:06.926 --> 00:07:09.262 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
In a grrrreat big forest!

00:07:09.346 --> 00:07:11.056 position:50% align:center
But Usao- <i>kun</i> might
get kicked out

00:07:11.139 --> 00:07:14.059 position:50% align:center
'cause he's been
a bear-y bad bunny.

00:07:15.226 --> 00:07:16.519 position:50% align:center
But that's so sad.

00:07:16.603 --> 00:07:17.645 position:50% align:center
Are you gonna be okay?

00:07:17.729 --> 00:07:19.689 position:50% align:center
Usao- <i>kun</i> has it pretty rough.

00:07:19.773 --> 00:07:21.775 position:50% align:center
Um, if the forest kicks you out,

00:07:21.858 --> 00:07:24.694 position:50% align:center
I can ask my mommy if we
could adopt you, okay?

00:07:24.778 --> 00:07:25.945 position:50% align:center
Yeah, me, too!

00:07:26.029 --> 00:07:27.864 position:50% align:center
And if she says no,
I'm gonna build

00:07:27.947 --> 00:07:29.407 position:50% align:center
a little house for
you in our yard,

00:07:29.491 --> 00:07:31.326 position:50% align:center
right next to
Poochie's doghouse!

00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:32.660 position:50% align:center
[BOY B]
I wanna help, too!

00:07:32.744 --> 00:07:34.746 position:50% align:center
[GIRL D] I'll ask Mom
if we can have a bunny!

00:07:34.829 --> 00:07:36.623 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
You guys.

00:07:39.209 --> 00:07:42.170 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] I think
Uramichi's having feelings.

00:07:42.253 --> 00:07:44.881 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
What? Is he sick?

00:07:44.964 --> 00:07:46.299 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
I'm just picturing these kids

00:07:46.383 --> 00:07:48.635 position:50% align:center
blowing their rent on pachinko.

00:07:48.718 --> 00:07:50.345 position:50% align:center
And getting ditched
on a group date,

00:07:50.428 --> 00:07:52.097 position:50% align:center
and drinking themselves
into oblivion,

00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:53.598 position:50% align:center
and passing out by the road,

00:07:53.682 --> 00:07:55.475 position:50% align:center
and having to explain
to the cops the next day

00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:58.269 position:50% align:center
that they're pantsless 'cause
someone stole their clothes.

00:07:58.353 --> 00:07:59.479 position:50% align:center
And I weep.

00:07:59.562 --> 00:08:01.398 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Why was that so specific?

00:08:01.481 --> 00:08:04.192 position:50% align:center
And why does it feel like
I just made my mom cry?

00:08:04.275 --> 00:08:06.528 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
Why do you think?

00:08:06.611 --> 00:08:08.488 position:50% align:center
[EDEI]
Good hustle, everyone!

00:08:09.489 --> 00:08:11.741 position:50% align:center
[KAYO]
You wanna try some detox tea?

00:08:11.825 --> 00:08:12.659 position:50% align:center
Oh, for sure! Did...

00:08:12.742 --> 00:08:14.035 position:50% align:center
So, Uramichi.

00:08:14.119 --> 00:08:16.579 position:50% align:center
I hope we're gonna be seeing
you at the after party!

00:08:16.663 --> 00:08:20.208 position:50% align:center
Well, um, I kinda had
plans to... go home.

00:08:20.291 --> 00:08:21.376 position:50% align:center
[DEREKIDA]
Man, that...

00:08:21.459 --> 00:08:22.502 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
You ever come up with a solution

00:08:22.585 --> 00:08:24.212 position:50% align:center
for your rent problem?

00:08:24.295 --> 00:08:25.797 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Hmm...

00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:29.467 position:50% align:center
Ooh! Hey, Iketeru, buddy!

00:08:29.551 --> 00:08:31.052 position:50% align:center
Oh, hey.

00:08:31.136 --> 00:08:33.346 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Could I borrow
some of the money, please?

00:08:33.430 --> 00:08:34.556 position:50% align:center
How much do you need?

00:08:34.639 --> 00:08:36.641 position:50% align:center
[UTANO, KUMATANI]
Don't give it to him!

00:08:36.725 --> 00:08:40.478 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
I worry about you. I really do.

00:08:40.562 --> 00:08:43.231 position:50% align:center
How'd you manage to
survive to adulthood?

00:08:43.314 --> 00:08:44.691 position:50% align:center
[IKETERU]
Huh?

00:08:44.774 --> 00:08:46.901 position:50% align:center
The lesson is, keep a
budget and plan ahead

00:08:46.985 --> 00:08:49.654 position:50% align:center
so you're not gambling
with your rent money!

00:08:50.697 --> 00:08:52.032 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
So we're calling it here?

00:08:52.115 --> 00:08:54.701 position:50% align:center
I'm literally gonna be homeless.

00:08:54.784 --> 00:08:57.537 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
<i>Uramichi Oniisan</i> !

00:09:00.874 --> 00:09:01.958 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
Does it ever feel like

00:09:02.042 --> 00:09:03.543 position:50% align:center
all that critical-thinking
crap we learned

00:09:03.626 --> 00:09:06.296 position:50% align:center
gets tossed out the
window in real life?

00:09:06.379 --> 00:09:08.673 position:50% align:center
You all right, man?
You sound pretty tired.

00:09:08.757 --> 00:09:11.551 position:50% align:center
It's a bit concerning to
hear that coming from you.

00:09:11.634 --> 00:09:14.596 position:50% align:center
Um. Sorry.

00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:16.848 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Yeah.

00:09:16.931 --> 00:09:18.433 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] We're just
expected not to talk about

00:09:18.516 --> 00:09:20.560 position:50% align:center
hypocrisy and unfairness.

00:09:20.643 --> 00:09:23.438 position:50% align:center
Is it really worth letting
myself be corrupted?

00:09:23.521 --> 00:09:24.773 position:50% align:center
Oh, cool.

00:09:24.856 --> 00:09:27.275 position:50% align:center
So I look corrupted to you,
is what you're saying.

00:09:27.359 --> 00:09:30.945 position:50% align:center
I dunno, but you do look like
you're putting up with a lot.

00:09:31.029 --> 00:09:32.322 position:50% align:center
I guess.

00:09:32.405 --> 00:09:34.532 position:50% align:center
Honestly, there have been
a few things bugging me,

00:09:34.616 --> 00:09:36.493 position:50% align:center
even before I messed up my back.

00:09:36.576 --> 00:09:38.370 position:50% align:center
Wait, what happened
to your back?

00:09:38.453 --> 00:09:40.372 position:50% align:center
I was doing my normal
weight routine

00:09:40.455 --> 00:09:43.249 position:50% align:center
when all of a sudden, I felt
a twinge in my lower back,

00:09:43.333 --> 00:09:45.752 position:50% align:center
and I realized I'd
double-loaded my bar.

00:09:45.835 --> 00:09:47.921 position:50% align:center
I mean, who hasn't
done that, right?

00:09:48.004 --> 00:09:49.881 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
Most people, probably.

00:09:49.964 --> 00:09:52.592 position:50% align:center
Huh? Really?

00:09:52.676 --> 00:09:56.971 position:50% align:center
But anyway, I know how much our
program means to all those kids.

