[MC A] So, now it's time for
Uramichi Oniisan and his friends

00:18:56.302 --> 00:18:59.389 position:50% align:center
to draw their dads for us,
too, live and in person!

00:18:59.472 --> 00:19:03.226 position:50% align:center
Huh? Hey, uh, I don't think
the script mentioned that.

00:19:03.309 --> 00:19:05.687 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Since when do we gotta draw?

00:19:05.770 --> 00:19:07.647 position:50% align:center
I bet all these boys
and girls wanna know

00:19:07.731 --> 00:19:10.066 position:50% align:center
what your dads are like,
too, don'tcha, kids?

00:19:10.150 --> 00:19:11.151 position:50% align:center
[KIDS]
Yeah!

00:19:11.234 --> 00:19:12.318 position:50% align:center
[MC A]
I knew it!

00:19:12.402 --> 00:19:14.237 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
She's working this crowd hard.

00:19:15.280 --> 00:19:18.742 position:50% align:center
Dear old dad!
I hope I draw him okay!

00:19:18.825 --> 00:19:20.035 position:50% align:center
Question, guys.

00:19:20.118 --> 00:19:21.786 position:50% align:center
Do you remember what your
dads' faces look like?

00:19:21.870 --> 00:19:25.331 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] I mean, I think I
mostly know what he looks like?

00:19:25.415 --> 00:19:27.459 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] Doesn't mean
I can draw him, though.

00:19:27.542 --> 00:19:28.918 position:50% align:center
Why are you acting
like you don't know

00:19:29.002 --> 00:19:31.338 position:50% align:center
how to draw your
dad's face, Oniisan?

00:19:31.421 --> 00:19:33.757 position:50% align:center
As you get older, you tend
to spend less and less time

00:19:33.840 --> 00:19:35.675 position:50% align:center
looking closely at
your dad's face,

00:19:35.759 --> 00:19:38.011 position:50% align:center
so it gets harder to remember!

00:19:38.094 --> 00:19:39.971 position:50% align:center
Will I stop liking him?

00:19:40.055 --> 00:19:41.765 position:50% align:center
No, you'll still like him!

00:19:41.848 --> 00:19:44.809 position:50% align:center
But you will feel awkward
just staring at him.

00:19:46.936 --> 00:19:48.021 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
That's a dad.

00:19:48.104 --> 00:19:49.397 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Yeah, I'm finished.

00:19:49.481 --> 00:19:52.901 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI]
Um. You're in character, guys.

00:19:52.984 --> 00:19:56.780 position:50% align:center
And your dads look
kinda... human-ish.

00:20:00.825 --> 00:20:02.535 position:50% align:center
[BOY F]
Those look like regular dads.

00:20:02.619 --> 00:20:04.996 position:50% align:center
[TAKKUN] Wait, you guys are a
bear and a bunny, aren't you?

00:20:05.080 --> 00:20:06.706 position:50% align:center
Shouldn't your dads
be the same things?

00:20:06.790 --> 00:20:08.583 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
My dad is a bear, fur sure!

00:20:08.667 --> 00:20:09.793 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
If he's not a bunny,

00:20:09.876 --> 00:20:12.504 position:50% align:center
then why do his ears
stand so high, hip-hop?

00:20:12.587 --> 00:20:14.130 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI] I started thinking
about how long it's been

00:20:14.214 --> 00:20:16.424 position:50% align:center
since I've seen him
and got hyper-focused.

00:20:16.508 --> 00:20:19.552 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] I have never thought
about my dad that hard.

00:20:19.636 --> 00:20:21.054 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Oh, uh, hey!

00:20:21.137 --> 00:20:24.683 position:50% align:center
Let's hop over and have a look
at Uramichi Oniisan's dad!

00:20:24.766 --> 00:20:27.352 position:50% align:center
Hippity-hey! That sure
looks like a dad.

00:20:27.435 --> 00:20:28.937 position:50% align:center
Ah! God!

00:20:29.020 --> 00:20:30.939 position:50% align:center
Dude. This is horrifying!

00:20:31.022 --> 00:20:32.315 position:50% align:center
What are we lookin' at here?

00:20:32.399 --> 00:20:34.984 position:50% align:center
My dad was a very strict man.

00:20:35.068 --> 00:20:37.487 position:50% align:center
When I was little,
he'd fling me onto the mat

00:20:37.570 --> 00:20:39.072 position:50% align:center
if I skipped training.

00:20:39.155 --> 00:20:41.408 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] You're the ragdoll
he's flingin' around?

00:20:41.491 --> 00:20:43.660 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] It was more than
my little sister could handle,

00:20:43.743 --> 00:20:45.245 position:50% align:center
and she left home at 16.

00:20:45.328 --> 00:20:47.872 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Uh, oh. So the
other one's your sister. Heh.

00:20:47.956 --> 00:20:49.958 position:50% align:center
I don't think you'd
ever mentioned her.

00:20:50.041 --> 00:20:53.378 position:50% align:center
Doesn't it make you feel sad
that you had a dad like that?

00:20:53.461 --> 00:20:54.754 position:50% align:center
I don't know what it
would have been like

00:20:54.838 --> 00:20:56.965 position:50% align:center
having a different dad,
but if I had,

00:20:57.048 --> 00:20:59.759 position:50% align:center
I bet I wouldn't be here
talking to you now.

00:20:59.843 --> 00:21:01.803 position:50% align:center
We all tend to dwell
on past mistakes

00:21:01.886 --> 00:21:03.013 position:50% align:center
and what could've been,

00:21:03.096 --> 00:21:05.265 position:50% align:center
but none of us has more
than one life to live,

00:21:05.348 --> 00:21:08.018 position:50% align:center
so we can only guess how
things would've turned out.

00:21:08.101 --> 00:21:11.271 position:50% align:center
We have to look forward
and try to find happiness,

00:21:11.354 --> 00:21:14.774 position:50% align:center
because that is our proof
that we made the right choice.

00:21:14.858 --> 00:21:16.109 position:50% align:center
Your mommies and
daddies have made

00:21:16.192 --> 00:21:18.945 position:50% align:center
wrong turns in their lives
just like everyone else,

00:21:19.029 --> 00:21:20.697 position:50% align:center
but they can't turn around,

00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:24.409 position:50% align:center
so you kids have to find the
way forward for yourselves.

00:21:24.492 --> 00:21:27.078 position:50% align:center
Even if we can't live
for the sake of others,

00:21:27.162 --> 00:21:29.039 position:50% align:center
I think it's best if
we can at least live

00:21:29.122 --> 00:21:31.916 position:50% align:center
without blaming them
for their missteps.

00:23:04.342 --> 00:23:06.011 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
Good job, team!

00:23:06.094 --> 00:23:10.348 position:50% align:center
Let's go grab a drink, Uramichi!
You, too, Kumatani!

00:23:10.432 --> 00:23:13.101 position:50% align:center
Before we go, let's
play rock-paper-scissors.

00:23:13.184 --> 00:23:15.103 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
What? Why?

00:23:16.062 --> 00:23:18.231 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] Listen,
I want you to throw after me

00:23:18.314 --> 00:23:20.066 position:50% align:center
and lose on purpose.

00:23:20.150 --> 00:23:22.736 position:50% align:center
Huh? Yeah. 'Kay.

00:23:22.819 --> 00:23:25.113 position:50% align:center
Here goes. Ready and throw.

00:23:25.196 --> 00:23:25.822 position:50% align:center
Throw.

00:23:25.905 --> 00:23:27.365 position:50% align:center
Ready and throw.

00:23:27.449 --> 00:23:28.783 position:50% align:center
Throw.

00:23:28.867 --> 00:23:30.910 position:50% align:center
--[URAMICHI] Throw. Throw.
--[USAHARA] Throw. Throw.

00:23:30.994 --> 00:23:32.037 position:50% align:center
--Throw.
--Throw.

00:23:32.120 --> 00:23:33.788 position:50% align:center
--Throw.
--Throw.

00:23:35.457 --> 00:23:39.419 position:50% align:center
Heh. I like this version.
Makes me feel like a winner.

00:23:39.502 --> 00:23:41.504 position:50% align:center
[URAMICHI] I'll go for drinks
if you take the balloon.

00:23:41.588 --> 00:23:44.257 position:50% align:center
Ah. Bro, why would I
wanna take the balloon?

00:23:44.341 --> 00:23:46.301 position:50% align:center
Wait, Kumatani,
I'll play you normal

00:23:46.384 --> 00:23:47.510 position:50% align:center
rock-paper-scissors
and the loser has to--

00:23:47.594 --> 00:23:48.970 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
No way.

00:23:49.054 --> 00:23:50.597 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA] Wait, c-come on,
just this one time, please?

00:23:50.680 --> 00:23:51.598 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
Nope.

00:23:51.681 --> 00:23:52.724 position:50% align:center
[USAHARA]
This one single time!

00:23:52.807 --> 00:23:54.225 position:50% align:center
[KUMATANI]
Not happening.